JOHANNESBURG – A cash box vault exploded at the hands of a G4S officer in Sandton mall, centre management confirmed on Saturday. "Sandton City Centre Management can confirm a cash box vault that has burst at ...shopping centre at around 14h15 on 2 December, 2017. Management can confirm that the cash box was being carried by an authorized G4S officer at the time of the incident," a statement said.  The centre's management said that the incident is not related to robbery and that operations are going on as normal.  The area has been cordoned off for safety reasons. But the mall is operating as normal. eNCA